), 3 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">C, D</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
The specimens examined in this study agree well the re-description of 
<bibRefCitation author="Hutchings, PA" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Australian Museum" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="241 - 274" refId="B21" refString="Hutchings, PA, Reid, A, Wilson, R, 1991. Perinereis (Polychaeta, Nereididae) from Australia, with redescriptions of six additional species. Records of the Australian Museum 43: 241 - 274" title="Perinereis (Polychaeta, Nereididae) from Australia, with redescriptions of six additional species." volume="43" year="1991">Hutchings et al. (1991)</bibRefCitation>
of this species. This is one of the largest of the wawo nereidids. The specimens reported as 
<taxonomicName genus="Perineris" lsidName="Perineris cultrifera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="cultrifera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Perineris cultrifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Martens, JM" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Institut und Zoologische Museum der Universitaet Hamburg" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="7 - 34" refId="B24" refString="Martens, JM, Heuer, U, Hartmann-Schrӧder, G, 1995. Mas-senschwӓrmen des Suedsee-Palolowurms (Palola viridis Gray) und weiterer Polychaeten wie Lysidice oele Horst and Lumbrineris natans n. sp. auf Ambon (Molukken; Indonesien). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Institut und Zoologische Museum der Universitaet Hamburg 92: 7 - 34" title="Mas-senschw ӓrmen des Suedsee-Palolowurms (Palola viridis Gray) und weiterer Polychaeten wie Lysidice oele Horst and Lumbrineris natans n. sp. auf Ambon (Molukken; Indonesien)." volume="92" year="1995">Martens et al. (1995)</bibRefCitation>
are most likely 
<taxonomicName genus="Perineris" lsidName="Perineris helleri" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="helleri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Perineris helleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as they fit well the paragnath number and pattern described here for this species (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Hutchings, PA" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Australian Museum" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="241 - 274" refId="B21" refString="Hutchings, PA, Reid, A, Wilson, R, 1991. Perinereis (Polychaeta, Nereididae) from Australia, with redescriptions of six additional species. Records of the Australian Museum 43: 241 - 274" title="Perinereis (Polychaeta, Nereididae) from Australia, with redescriptions of six additional species." volume="43" year="1991">Hutchings et al. 1991</bibRefCitation>
), although there is a discrepancy in the number of anterior unmodified chaetigers: 
<bibRefCitation author="Martens, JM" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Institut und Zoologische Museum der Universitaet Hamburg" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="7 - 34" refId="B24" refString="Martens, JM, Heuer, U, Hartmann-Schrӧder, G, 1995. Mas-senschwӓrmen des Suedsee-Palolowurms (Palola viridis Gray) und weiterer Polychaeten wie Lysidice oele Horst and Lumbrineris natans n. sp. auf Ambon (Molukken; Indonesien). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Institut und Zoologische Museum der Universitaet Hamburg 92: 7 - 34" title="Mas-senschw ӓrmen des Suedsee-Palolowurms (Palola viridis Gray) und weiterer Polychaeten wie Lysidice oele Horst and Lumbrineris natans n. sp. auf Ambon (Molukken; Indonesien)." volume="92" year="1995">Martens et al. (1995)</bibRefCitation>
report this as 14 and 18 (male and female respectively), but our observations for this species are 17 and 19-20 (ditto). We believe Martens et al. may have confused 
<taxonomicName genus="Perineris" lsidName="Perineris helleri" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="helleri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Perineris helleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName genus="Perineris" lsidName="Perineris nigropunctata" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="nigropunctata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Perineris nigropunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which were also found in their samples, as the latter has about 14 and 17 anterior unmodified chaetigers for male and female respectively (see following account).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
